===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|akène|lang=fr}} and its source, {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|achena|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἀ-||a-|lang=grc}} + {{term|χαίνω||to gape|tr=chainō|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/əˈkiːn/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|botany|lang=en}} A small, dry, [[indehiscent]] fruit, containing a single seed, as in the [[buttercup]].

====Usage notes====
Early botanists referred to ''achenes'' as ''naked seeds''.

